</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p ">Some print modes contain multiple print strategies that offer optimized performance for specific media conditions. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Refer to the Media Verification Protocol (MVP) to choose the best available strategy. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Profiles provided via the Media Guide have a predefined setting. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
</p><note id="GUID-55A6B759-4A67-4E52-BC0A-F00F39E47B20" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The differences in productivity between M3 and M5 series are based on a different print carriage speed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The M5 print carriage runs on +/- 1.4 m/s, M3 on +/- 1 m/s. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Exceptions are made for the above rule within the M3 during: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">gloss specialty, they are kept the same 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Backlit &amp; backlit density and all multilayers also runs on 1.4 m/s 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Single layer white run on 1 m/s 
</p></li></ul></note></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-EF42FFF3-C6AF-4939-AE5C-9EB2061E0E1B.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Image Quality</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
